Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.56,0:01:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsunoko Production
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.35,0:01:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Flower bloom...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.29,0:01:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Flower bloom...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.81,0:01:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Flower bloom...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.12,0:02:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,At 3:00 am on December 8th, 1941, at the same time as the Pacific War began,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.66,0:02:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant General Sakai, commander of the 23rd Army of the Japanese Army,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.29,0:02:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who received a coded telegram of the successful landing on the Malay Peninsula,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.18,0:02:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately gathered at the border of the Kowloon Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.22,0:02:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He ordered 30,000 soldiers to attack Hong Kong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.63,0:02:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Hong Kong (Episode Six)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.42,0:03:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese army had thoroughly investigated, planned, and prepared for the capture of Hong Kong in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.49,0:03:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy has fortified a major position named "Gin Drinkers Line".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,From Shau Kei Wan to Golden Hill, Shing Mun Reservoir to Lion Rock, to stop our troops on the Kowloon Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.60,0:03:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,"Gin Drinkers Line" was a strangely-named line of defense. It means one who over drinks gin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.01,0:03:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy commander, Major General Maltby, seems to have recently placed the British 2nd Royal Scots Battalion,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.26,0:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,India's 2nd and 14th Punjam Battalion, and the 5th and 7th Radifoot on this Gin Drinkers Line yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.00,0:03:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in anticipation of the start of the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.88,0:03:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it seems that our army is by far the dominant force.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.82,0:03:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's fight openly in an orthodox method.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.92,0:03:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How many days will it take for the first artillery to reach the enemy's main position?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.52,0:03:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It will take a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.90,0:03:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Can it be done in a week?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.56,0:03:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Lets do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.67,0:03:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.08,0:04:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The preparation period for breaking through the Gin Drinkers Line is one week.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.84,0:04:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The focus of the bombardment is between Lion Rock and Golden Hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.29,0:04:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Please shell the middle of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.48,0:04:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Lets hit those 24cm howitzers with all our might.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.11,0:04:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If we crush one place, we can attack from the side and the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.94,0:04:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, the division's main force will be placed to the east and west of Tai Mo Shan,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.78,0:04:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will break through the Gin Drinkers Line at a moment's notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It is exactly the same tactic as the Siege of Port Arthur of the Russo-Japanese War,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.46,0:04:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hong Kong is divided into the Kowloon Peninsula, which borders the Chinese continent, and Hong Kong Island. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.38,0:04:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There were approximately 12,000 troops centered on two battalions each from the UK, India,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.94,0:04:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and Canada under the command of Major General Maltby.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.12,0:05:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese attack was carried out as planned, and the British were immediately hit everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.42,0:05:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the British Army was also expecting to defend the Gin Drinkers Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.50,0:05:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese army made a cautious operational plan to completely crush the British position by bombardment,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.06,0:05:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and then advance the troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.90,0:05:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the commander of the front line decided to have his subordinate,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.08,0:05:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Toichi Wakabayashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.04,0:05:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,lead a squad on reconnaissance to search for the British position in the highlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.32,0:06:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.96,0:06:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It seems to be an observation post.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.88,0:06:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.90,0:06:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It is dangerous With this moonlight the enemy will soon discover us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.04,0:06:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it's God's help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.42,0:06:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This lieutenant had risen from the ranks
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.52,0:06:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and had sufficient practical experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.90,0:07:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.44,0:07:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Whats going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.40,0:07:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To break through the Gin Drinkers Line, we must first bring down this observation post.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.74,0:07:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.49,0:07:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant, no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take it by surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't. It's reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.55,0:07:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,With only 21 soldiers, in addition...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"In addition"? Spit it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.50,0:07:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Our mission is reconnaissance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.62,0:07:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is insubordinate {HA: This is an act of disobedience.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.71,0:07:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. Just get rid of moles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.21,0:07:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“On the battlefield, there are many things that require arbitrary judgment”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.16,0:07:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Flexibility is needed on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.23,0:07:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a great deal of need for dogmatism,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.19,0:07:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is not always considered that dogmatism violates military regulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.10,0:07:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.46,0:07:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.69,0:07:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.73,0:07:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an easy job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.11,0:07:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.94,0:07:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an easy job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.96,0:07:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.53,0:08:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, once I jump in first, then you guys also jump in line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.08,0:08:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot anything that moves from side to side, they all seem to be enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.80,0:09:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How many Japanese troops are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe 200 or 300, 400 or 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.35,0:09:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There are only 100 garrison members.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.65,0:09:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately ask the captain for support.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.74,0:09:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Call him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.30,0:09:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.32,0:09:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.66,0:09:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.40,0:09:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.58,0:09:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Be calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.03,0:10:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.36,0:10:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.66,0:10:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.41,0:10:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.72,0:10:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.90,0:10:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Our scouts ran into the enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.86,0:10:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and are in a terrible firefight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.62,0:10:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not good. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.74,0:10:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they aimed to "steal a march on one's rival."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.43,0:10:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It is unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.42,0:10:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately, with the support of the 2nd Battalion,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.93,0:10:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,attack with the 3rd Battalion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.08,0:10:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.44,0:10:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that would mess up the military's operational plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.84,0:10:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let the scouts die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.92,0:10:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the intention of the division leader...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.88,0:10:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.28,0:10:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.00,0:10:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They will know military discipline!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.02,0:10:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately return the scout unit and punish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.76,0:10:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.42,0:10:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The military is always acting on a prudent operational plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.54,0:10:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not allow rash actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.22,0:11:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, Let's get in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.20,0:11:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.98,0:11:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.32,0:11:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, give me support!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.00,0:11:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to this sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.20,0:12:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to this sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.69,0:12:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No. The Japanese army has arrived here too! Counterattack is impossible. Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.94,0:12:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you say "retreat", all exits are suppressed by the Japanese army.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.04,0:12:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I hate this kind of position.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.04,0:13:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.06,0:13:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.92,0:13:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Look
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.11,0:13:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.32,0:13:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.18,0:13:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that it was not necessary to return the occupied position to the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.87,0:13:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,so I asked the front line commander to stop further attacks and only secure the position we stole...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It they do such things often, our military's operational plans will be ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.04,0:13:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They should be punished. Violations of discipline are serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.38,0:13:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,However, they made the operation, which our army thought would take a week, happen in just one night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.98,0:13:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, why did we plan and prepare for the operation?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.05,0:14:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Allowing such a runaway action will only confuse the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.70,0:14:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it good? Being flexible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.34,0:14:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This took a weight off my shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.76,0:14:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.88,0:14:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the problem of punishing the scouts will be the first issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.08,0:14:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Regarding that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.36,0:14:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it is true that they made a big hole in the Gin Drinkers line,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.14,0:14:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the British troops are gradually retreating over their front line.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.26,0:14:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the commanders of the front lines insist that they should take advantage of this period,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.76,0:14:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and start their advance at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.10,0:14:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.14,0:14:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.76,0:14:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.94,0:14:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.64,0:14:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We will immediately change the plan
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.28,0:14:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and launch a mass attack over the entire front line.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move the entire British army to Hong Kong Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.38,0:15:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek’s allied forces will attack the Japanese from behind on the Kowloon Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.06,0:15:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It is more effective than defending the Kowloon Peninsula and struggling any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.43,0:16:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.22,0:16:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,order all the soldiers on the Kowloon Peninsula to pull up to Hong Kong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.50,0:16:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The breakthrough of the Gin Drinker's Line, which was initially thought to take a week,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.34,0:16:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,was completed in just three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.48,0:16:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kowloon Peninsula was subdued and Japanese troops entered Hong Kong's Kowloon District.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.42,0:16:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At 9:05 am on December 13th,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.86,0:17:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the Japanese staff landed on Hong Kong Island to plead with the British women to encourage surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.58,0:17:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.66,0:17:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the British reply was only one word:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.88,0:17:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"Never"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.72,0:17:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, they never surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.00,0:17:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese attack was launched again and the air raids continued.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.02,0:17:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It was more intense than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,On December 17th, the Japanese army again recommended surrender. But,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.96,0:18:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governor of Hong Kong and the military commander,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.10,0:18:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutely refused to enter into negotiations regarding the surrender of Hong Kong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.93,0:18:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We will also notify you that we are no longer ready to be contacted by the Japanese military regarding this matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.64,0:18:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A squall is likely to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.62,0:18:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The moonrise tonight is late.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,9 o'clock tonight, start the landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.22,0:18:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, my division has Lieutenant Reizo Koike, who won the breaststroke at the Los Angeles Olympic Games.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.93,0:18:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The lieutenant's unit will swim in and confuse the enemy base.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.78,0:18:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.76,0:19:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,With that black smoke, they would not be able to see the sea from the British position.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.96,0:19:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, in this weather, the sea is completely dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.70,0:19:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Its the same as the Gin Drinkers line's breakthrough strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.54,0:19:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's land all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.36,0:19:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese army started landing on Hong Kong Island, at 9 pm
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.78,0:19:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the British side hardly noticed It,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.08,0:19:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,even as the Japanese army approaching to 90m.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.24,0:19:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the second observation post.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.42,0:19:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing out of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.50,0:19:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They even made such a report.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.78,0:20:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese army landed successfully,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.90,0:20:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.80,0:20:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the counterattack of the British troops who had been cut off from their escape route was fierce.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.26,0:20:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The power plant, an important base,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.56,0:20:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,was also protected by 70 British and French businessmen living in Hong Kong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.83,0:20:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite having military careers, the youngest was only 55 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.78,0:20:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.64,0:20:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,even after the retreat of the Indian Rajput battalion, their troops successfully held the power plant for a whole day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.26,0:20:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of World War I, it wasn't like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.06,0:20:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This medal of mine was given during the Spanish War.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.58,0:20:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.88,0:20:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The Indian Rajput Battalion is retreating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.88,0:21:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They are pitiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.24,0:21:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind. We defend here until we die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.86,0:21:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best. Chiang Kai-shek’s army will soon attack the Japanese from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.46,0:21:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.66,0:21:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the allied army of Chiang Kai-shek, who they relied on, did not arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.16,0:21:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It moved far beyond the border from west to east and disappeared into the interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.64,0:21:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,British soldiers were in despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.08,0:21:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Governor, the reservoir on the east side of Nicholson has finally fallen to the Japanese army.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.68,0:22:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Citizens are fleeing Hong Kong one after another in search of water and food.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.80,0:22:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot continue the fight any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.44,0:22:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If we fight any more, we will kill all the citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.62,0:22:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,December 25th, 5:20 pm
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.09,0:22:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governor of Hong Kong and Major General Maltby decided to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.86,0:22:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He visited the Japanese military headquarters at the Peninsula Hotel in Kowloon District.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.68,0:22:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Christmas day
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.62,0:23:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The British surrendered in the candlelight, as if celebrating a holy night.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.16,0:23:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,For that reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.50,0:23:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the feeling of defeat in the Governor of Hong Kong was strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.32,0:23:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop It!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.24,0:23:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop It!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.32,0:23:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The Battle of Hong Kong, which was supposed to take four weeks, ended in almost half the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.84,0:23:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,These quick victories include problems that the commander of the group must always keep in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.56,0:23:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The reckless attack of this young junior commander blew away the looseness of command
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.22,0:23:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that was likely to result from overly cautious operations, and paved the way for victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.00,0:23:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When you come into contact with the momentum of your subordinates, {Seems like this should be split with the next line, not really sure what goes where though}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.16,0:23:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,can you further encourage that momentum depending on the situation and exert it over the entire organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.10,0:23:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It always depends on the good decisions of senior commanders.
